We recommend and the Management agreed that the Acting MGSO:
strictly observe the policies, and procedures provided in the NGAS Manual for record-keeping, monitoring, and reporting of inventories, particularly in the use and maintenance of the prescribed inventory forms and reports such as the Stock Card, Requisition and Issue Slip, and the Report on the Physical Count of Inventories;
conduct a physical count of inventory items per type and report the same in the Report on the Physical Count of Inventories, using the form prescribed by the NGAS Manual for LGUs, and submit to the Auditor concerned not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively;
take custody of all supplies and materials received and control their release through the use of the Requisition and Issue Slips, particularly on the construction materials inventory, which must be released based on the need of the requisitioning office only;
submit to the Municipal Accounting Office the Acceptance and Inspection Report, together with the Delivery Receipt and other supporting documents, after inspection of the supplies and materials received for recording in the ledger cards;
provide thorough orientation to assigned personnel on inventory management practices and procedures, particularly on the use and maintenance of prescribed inventory forms and reports; and
conduct a benchmarking activity on the use of inventory software for supply and property management.
We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant record the delivery of supplies and materials in the appropriate ledger cards upon receipt of the Acceptance and Inspection Report, together with the Delivery Receipt and other supporting documents.
We further recommended that the Municipal Mayor consider establishing a fully operational Municipal General Services Office (MGSO) to take over general services functions currently handled by the Municipal Treasurer, which are in addition to treasury-related duties.

