The preparation of updated stock cards by the Office of the Municipal Agriculturist to be matched/reconciled regularly with the ledger cards of the accounting unit and discrepancy(ies), if any, shall be immediately verified and adjusted;

The Office of the Municipal Agriculturist to monitor and investigate all mortalities of dispersal animals, update their records and copy furnish the accounting department to facilitate reconciliation and reflect the correct balance of the account Breeding Stocks; 

The Municipal Mayor to direct the Office of the Municipal Agriculturist to substantiate all claims of loss through death of said animals with complete documentary attachments upon filing of a request for relief from accountability for the proper disposition thereof pursuant to Section 151 of COA Circular No. 92-386 to the audit team; and

The concerned officials and employees conduct regular inspection of stocks dispersed and physical inventory of existing animals in accordance with existing accounting and auditing rules and regulations. Periodic reconciliation of accounting and property records shall be made and discrepancy (ies), if any, should be immediately verified and adjusted.

