observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipality take the following courses of action:

Conduct physical inventory of the property, plant and equipment and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE);

Conduct reconciliation of the RPCPPE with the Accounting records and submit the same to COA;

Prepare a separate report on unserviceable and obsolete, including those assets which, though still serviceable, are no longer used in operation using the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP); and

Require the Disposal Committee to plan the disposal of unserviceable properties in accordance with the guidelines set under Section 79 of PD 1445, including requesting for assistance from COA technical inspectors.

We recommended that the Municipality Mayor direct the responsible officials of the Municipality to:

Complete the annual physical inventory of the property, plant and equipment;
Prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE); 
Conduct reconciliation of the RPCPPE with the accounting records; and
Submit the RPCPPE to COA not later than January 31 of each year.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor should direct:

The Office of the Municipal Treasurer to keep custody of all inventoriable supplies after delivery and inspection of the same by the inspection committee;  
The Municipal Accounting Office to record all inventoriable supplies under their appropriate inventory accounts upon purchase based on the Acceptance and Inspection Report and other supporting documents;
The Municipal Agriculture Office to submit the pertinent withdrawal and/or acknowledgment receipts supporting the distribution of the agricultural supplies to the members of the beneficiary civil society organizations.

