We recommend that management do the following:

1. Prepare a separate report on unserviceable, fully depreciated assets, including those which, though still serviceable, are no longer used in operation, using the Inventory and Inspection Report on Unserviceable Property (IIRUP);

2. Advise the accounting and General Services Offices to reconcile the inventory report with the accounting records and to prepare subsidiary records thereof, which should be regularly updated;

3. Direct the Accounting  office to reclassify assets listed in the IIRUP, from Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE) to the Other Assets;

